features.description:
ACTION: add SQLite + Drizzle ORM to the existing Next.js scaffold.

FILES YOU MUST CREATE OR MODIFY (use Write/Edit):
- `lib/db.ts` — exports a Drizzle `db` instance backed by better-sqlite3, opening `data.sqlite` in the project root. Suggested content:
  ```ts
  import Database from 'better-sqlite3';
  import { drizzle } from 'drizzle-orm/better-sqlite3';
  const sqlite = new Database('data.sqlite');
  export const db = drizzle(sqlite);
  ```
- `drizzle.config.ts` — points at `./lib/schema.ts` (created in the next feature) and outputs to `./drizzle`. Suggested content:
  ```ts
  import type { Config } from 'drizzle-kit';
  export default { schema: './lib/schema.ts', out: './drizzle', dialect: 'sqlite', dbCredentials: { url: './data.sqlite' } } satisfies Config;
  ```

BASH COMMAND YOU MUST RUN:
- `npm install better-sqlite3 drizzle-orm` and `npm install -D drizzle-kit @types/better-sqlite3`.

The session is incomplete unless lib/db.ts AND drizzle.config.ts exist on disk and node_modules/better-sqlite3 exists. Reading package.json without writing files does NOT complete this feature.
